benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/paymentMethods - Retrieve account payment methods

covered: GET Method - Valid Request: Scenarios cover successful retrievals with various query parameters.
GET Method - Empty Response: Scenario for account with no payment methods returns empty array.
GET Method - Query Parameters: Multiple combinations tested (withPluginInfo, includedDeleted, pluginProperty, audit, etc.).
Authorization - 401: Scenario for missing authentication token exists.
Error Handling - 400/404/422/500-series: Scenarios cover invalid accountId (400), account not found (404), invalid audit (400), security test cases (400/422).
Performance/Recovery - Large dataset and retry: TC14 tests large result set with timing; TC19 tests transient dependency recovery.
Regression - Missing pluginInfo fix and backward compatibility: TC20, TC21 address regression and compatibility.
gaps: Pagination: No explicit tests for paging through results (page size, page token, total pages).
Authorization: No test explicitly covers 403 Forbidden for insufficient permissions or role-based access control.
Rate Limiting: No tests verifying behavior under high request load or throttling.
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or cache validation semantics.
Explicit 502 for dependent services in all plugin/info scenarios beyond plugin service unavailability (some coverage exists but not exhaustive).
recommendations: Add dedicated pagination tests (e.g., page/size, total pages, max page size, boundary conditions).
Add authorization scope tests confirming 403 when user lacks required permissions.
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to verify behavior under bursty traffic.
Add caching tests verifying ETag/Cache-Control headers and proper cache reevaluation.
Extend integration tests to cover broader plugin service failure modes (e.g., 502 across more scenarios).
